fuel efficiency.Description: The weight of a vehicle affects its fuel efficiency. Heavier vehicles generally have lower fuel efficiency.
The size of an engine can impact fuel efficiency. Smaller engines tend to be more fuel-efficient.
The aerodynamics of a vehicle play a significant role in fuel efficiency. Vehicles with better aerodynamics have higher fuel efficiency.
Maintaining proper tire pressure is important for fuel efficiency. Underinflated tires can decrease fuel efficiency.
